SUMMARY:IMPROMPTU LI - Some hills to Courtyard Cafe (28 R)
DESCRIPTION:Lancaster Bicycle Club (LBC) Meetup\n## Details\n\nRide Leader
 : Bruce Black\n\nA fun ride north and east of Lititz with not too much cli
 mbing. We will stop at Courtyard Cafe for food/beverage. The final portion
  of the course is on the Warwick Ephrata Trail. If trail conditions are to
 o wet or muddy we will decide on an alternate return route. The pace will 
 be 14 - 16 mph average with multiple stop and regroup points.\n\nCue and R
 ide with GPS links:\n[LI - Some hills to Courtyard Cafe (28 R)](https://ri
 dewithgps.com/routes/54536100?privacy_code=8Ut88osjaKPttzQbwLD2w3JK7h12bE5
 l)\n\nHelmets are mandatory\; please also plan to bring 1-2 water bottles\
 , and a basic repair kit (spare tube\, tire levers\, pump/CO2 inflator).\n
 Being a Meetup Member does not mean you are a club member. Use this link t
 o join the club.\n[https://www.lancasterbikeclub.net/content.aspx?page_id=
 60&club_id=257148](https://www.lancasterbikeclub.net/content.aspx?page_id=
 60&club_id=257148)\nYour RSVP is your agreement to abide by the club's Cod
 e of Conduct [https://lancbikeclub.clubexpress.com/content.aspx?page_id=22
 &club_id=257148&module_id=323984](https://lancbikeclub.clubexpress.com/con
 tent.aspx?page_id=22&club_id=257148&module_id=323984)\nand Rules of the Ro
 ad\n[https://lancbikeclub.clubexpress.com/content.aspx?](https://lancbikec
 lub.clubexpress.com/content.aspx?page_id=22&club_id=257148&module_id=32515
 9)
